{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"foregroundStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"style"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","text":"ShapeStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"style","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The color or pattern to use when filling in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"foreground elements. To indicate a specific value, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/image(_:sourceRect:scale:)"},{"text":", or one of the gradient","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types, like","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)"},{"text":". To set a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"style that’s relative to the containing view’s style, use one of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"semantic styles, like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/primary","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that uses the given foreground style."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this method to style"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"foreground content like text, shapes, and template images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(including symbols):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Image(systemName: \"triangle.fill\")","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 5)","        .frame(width: 40, height: 20)","}",".foregroundStyle(.teal)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above creates a row of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"elements:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use any style that conforms to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"like the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" color in the example above, or the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)"},{"text":" gradient","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shown below:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Text(\"Gradient Text\")","    .font(.largeTitle)","    .foregroundStyle(","        .linearGradient(","            colors: [.yellow, .blue],","            startPoint: .top,","            endPoint: .bottom","        )","    )"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to fill a single ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" instance with a style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape\/fill(style:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" shape modifier instead because it’s more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"efficient.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OpenSwiftUI creates a context-dependent render for a given style.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For example, a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"text":" that you load from an asset catalog","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can have different light and dark appearances, while some styles","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also vary by platform.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Hierarchical foreground styles like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/secondary"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"don’t impose a style of their own, but instead modify other styles.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In particular, they modify the primary","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"level of the current foreground style to the degree given by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the hierarchical style’s name.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To find the current foreground style to modify, OpenSwiftUI looks for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the innermost containing style that you apply with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foregroundStyle(_:)"},{"text":" or the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/foregroundColor(_:)"},{"text":" modifier.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you haven’t specified a style, OpenSwiftUI uses the default foreground","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"style, as in the following example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you add a foreground style on the enclosing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", the hierarchical styling responds accordingly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}",".foregroundStyle(.blue)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When you apply a custom style to a view, the view disables the vibrancy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"effect for foreground elements in that view, or in any of its child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"views, that it would otherwise gain from adding a background material","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"— for example, using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifier. However, hierarchical styles applied to the default foreground","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"don’t disable vibrancy.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/circle\/foregroundstyle(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE15foregroundStyleyQrqd__AA05ShapeF0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore6CircleV","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"foregroundStyle(_:)","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"iOS"},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS"},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"tvOS"},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"visionOS"},{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"watchOS"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/ShapeStyle\/ForegroundStyleModifier.swift#L112","fileName":"ForegroundStyleModifier.swift"},"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"foregroundStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15Open